My name is Ifeanyi Kenneth Okpoko.

0:19:03.320,0:19:08.560
I am the second son of the family.

0:19:08.560,0:19:16.580
I happen to be the most doubting of all the Thomases.

0:19:16.580,0:19:20.160
In the first place, I rarely go to church.

0:19:20.160,0:19:24.220
I have never been a church goer, I don’t even pray.

0:19:24.220,0:19:28.760
I just live as every other free man.

0:19:28.760,0:19:34.240
I just believe in the laws of nature; you do evil, evil comes to you; you do good, good comes to you.

0:19:34.240,0:19:36.020
I have always been a naturalist.

0:19:36.020,0:19:43.980
When I met my wife in Kano, she was introduced to me by a family I was supplying goods to.

0:19:43.980,0:19:47.020
That was a long time ago, in the year 2000.

0:19:47.020,0:20:05.860
One of the things she used to lure me into marrying her, was that she said that she was a Christian.

0:20:05.860,0:20:11.480
When talking to her, she would quote the book of James, etc.

0:20:11.480,0:20:14.640
Any conversation would end with Christ.

0:20:14.640,0:20:22.900
I thought that as I am not a Christian - I was a Christian by birth but not a practising one.

0:20:22.900,0:20:27.480
I decided to marry this woman who was very close to God.

0:20:27.480,0:20:36.220
It failed because the woman I thought would lead me to God, became something else after I married her.

0:20:36.220,0:20:40.060
When we moved to Lagos, she started worshipping in another place.

0:20:40.060,0:20:44.960
She went there every Sunday morning.

0:20:44.960,0:20:52.120
She would go to church singing praises but come back a wild creature.

0:20:52.120,0:20:55.000
She didn’t care about me or the family.

0:20:55.000,0:20:56.880
She would not care about my meal.

0:20:56.880,0:21:02.360
It continued until I became diabetic in 2005.

0:21:02.360,0:21:06.060
I told her about my health status and she didn't care.

0:21:06.060,0:21:07.660
She said that I could go and marry someone

0:21:07.660,0:21:12.120
who would take care of my diabetes that she didn't bargain for that.

0:21:12.120,0:21:14.960
As she got on with her career, it became worse.

0:21:14.960,0:21:16.780
She was working with a bank then.

0:21:16.780,0:21:19.860
After she started working with UBA.

0:21:19.860,0:21:24.820
As her career progressed she became more wild.

0:21:24.820,0:21:29.800
If I talked she would shout at me and if I threatened her with separation,

0:21:29.800,0:21:34.940
she would say that her job was better without a husband so she was ready to leave.

0:21:34.940,0:21:41.240
These things would be happening and each time I spoke with my dad he said that he wanted to come back

0:21:41.240,0:21:44.860
and that it appeared as if he and myself shared the same destiny.

0:21:44.860,0:21:49.420
I said no, that he just hand to come back; to know what was really going on.

0:21:49.420,0:21:55.300
When we were growing up, my dad would be talking about my mum being a witch but

0:21:55.300,0:21:59.820
I didn’t want to dwell on that because I didn’t know how to identify a witch.

0:21:59.820,0:22:05.640
I tried as much as possible to play my role as a son, both to my mother and father.

0:22:05.640,0:22:11.200
If I go to England, my father complains that his work is not good;

0:22:11.200,0:22:13.640
he doesn’t know what happens to his money.

0:22:13.640,0:22:15.680
Each time I leave him, I give him some money.

0:22:15.680,0:22:18.720
When I come back to Nigeria, I call him to see how he is.

0:22:18.720,0:22:24.460
If he needs money, from the little I have, I send to him like 2-3000 pounds for his upkeep.

0:22:24.460,0:22:26.460
I do the same thing for my mum.

0:22:26.460,0:22:31.520
